column1: What are the names of poker players, ordered ascending by the number of final tables they have made?
column2: SELECT T2.name FROM people AS T2 JOIN poker_player AS T1 ON T2.People_ID = T1.People_ID ORDER BY COUNT(.) ASC ASC'
column3: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN poker_player AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Final_Table_Made
column4: In which year were most departments established?
column5: Select age from department as T1 join management as T3 on T1.department_id = T3.departemnt_id Join head AS T2 on T2.head_id = T3.head_id Order BY Count(*) Desc Limit 1
column6: SELECT creation FROM department GROUP BY creation ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column1: What is last date created of votes from the state 'CA'?
column3: SELECT max(created) FROM votes WHERE state  =  'CA'
column4: List the most common type of Status across cities.
column5: GROUP BY city.status ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1'
column6: SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column1: What is the area code in which the most voters voted?
column3: SELECT T1.area_code FROM area_code_state AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.state  =  T2.state GROUP BY T1.area_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
column4: Show different publishers together with the number of publications they have.
column5: SELECT COUNT(*) ,DISTINCT(publication.Publisher) FROM publication'
column6: SELECT Publisher ,  COUNT(*) FROM publication GROUP BY Publisher

column1: What are the names of conductors, sorted descending by the number of years they have worked?
column2: SELECT conductor.name FROM conductor ORDER BY COUNT(.) ASC DESC'
column3: SELECT Name FROM conductor ORDER BY Year_of_Work DESC
column4: How many actors have appeared in each musical?
column5: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM musical WHERE  Actor_ID IN (SELECT Actor_ID  FROM musical) GROUP BY T2.musical_id'
column6: SELECT T2.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM actor AS T1 JOIN musical AS T2 ON T1.Musical_ID  =  T2.Musical_ID GROUP BY T1.Musical_ID

column1: Please show the different record companies and the corresponding number of orchestras.
column3: SELECT Record_Company ,  COUNT(*) FROM orchestra GROUP BY Record_Company
column4: Show different nominees and the number of musicals they have been nominated.
column5: SELECT COUNT(*) ,DISTINCT(musical.Nominee) FROM musical'
column6: SELECT Nominee ,  COUNT(*) FROM musical GROUP BY Nominee

column1: How many orchestras does each record company manage?
column2: SELECT COUNT(*) ,orchestra FROM orchestra GROUP BY orchestra'
column3: SELECT Record_Company ,  COUNT(*) FROM orchestra GROUP BY Record_Company
column4: Who are the nominees who have been nominated more than two times?
column5: SELECT nominee FROM musical AS T2 JOIN actor AS T1 ON T2.Musical_ID = T1.Musical_ID WHERE T1.Duration > two GROUP BY T1.duration HAVING COUNT(*)> 2'
column6: SELECT Nominee FROM musical GROUP BY Nominee HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

column1: List the names of orchestras that have no performance.
column2: SELECT conductor.name FROM conductor WHERE  Orchestra_ID NOT IN (SELECT Orchestra_ID  FROM performance)'
column3: SELECT Orchestra FROM orchestra WHERE Orchestra_ID NOT IN (SELECT Orchestra_ID FROM performance)
column4: For each journal_committee, find the editor name and the journal theme.
column5: SELECT FROM journal AS T2 JOIN journal_committee AS T3 ON T2.Journal_ID = T3.Journal_ID    JOIN editor AS T1 ON T1.Editor_ID = T3.Editor_ID   GROUP BY T2_committee.editor_id'
column6: SELECT T2.Name ,  T3.Theme FROM journal_committee AS T1 JOIN editor AS T2 ON T1.Editor_ID  =  T2.Editor_ID JOIN journal AS T3 ON T1.Journal_ID  =  T3.Journal_ID

column1: What are the orchestras that do not have any performances?
column2: SELECT T1 FROM show AS T2 JOIN orchestra AS T1 ON T2.Show_ID = T1.Conductor_ID'
column3: SELECT Orchestra FROM orchestra WHERE Orchestra_ID NOT IN (SELECT Orchestra_ID FROM performance)
column4: What are the names of different tracks, and how many races has each had?
column5: SELECT T2.name FROM track AS T2 JOIN race AS T1 ON T2.Track_ID = T1.Track_ID GROUP BY name'
column6: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM race AS T1 JOIN track AS T2 ON T1.track_id  =  T2.track_id GROUP BY T1.track_id

column4: Show the times used by climbers to climb mountains in Country Uganda.
column5: "SELECT time FROM mountain AS T2 JOIN climber AS T1 ON T2.Mountain_ID = T1.Mountain_ID WHERE T2.Height ' = Country Uganda'"
column6: SELECT T1.Time FROM climber AS T1 JOIN mountain AS T2 ON T1.Mountain_ID  =  T2.Mountain_ID WHERE T2.Country  =  "Uganda"

column4: List the hosts of performances in ascending order of attendance.
column5: SELECT T1.nationality FROM member AS T1 JOIN member_attendance AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID = T2.Member_ID ORDER BY  T1_attendance.T1_attendance ASC'
column6: SELECT HOST FROM performance ORDER BY Attendance ASC

column4: How many different teams have had eliminated wrestlers?

column4: Show names of shops and the carriers of devices they have in stock.

column6: SELECT T3.Shop_Name ,  T2.Carrier FROM stock AS T1 JOIN device AS T2 ON T1.Device_ID  =  T2.Device_ID JOIN shop AS T3 ON T1.Shop_ID  =  T3.Shop_ID

column4: Show names of shops that have more than one kind of device in stock.
column5: SELECT T2.shop_name FROM device AS T3 JOIN stock AS T1 ON T3.Device_ID = T1.Device_ID    JOIN shop AS T2 ON T2.Shop_ID = T1.Shop_ID   GROUP BY T1.stock HAVING COUNT(*)> 1'
column6: SELECT T2.Shop_Name FROM stock AS T1 JOIN shop AS T2 ON T1.Shop_ID  =  T2.Shop_ID GROUP BY T1.Shop_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

column4: Show the name of the shop that has the most kind of devices in stock.
column5: SELECT T3.shop_name FROM device AS T1 JOIN stock AS T2 ON T1.Device_ID = T2.Device_ID    JOIN shop AS T3 ON T3.Shop_ID = T2.Shop_ID   ORDER BY T2.T2 DESC LIMIT 1'
column6: SELECT T2.Shop_Name FROM stock AS T1 JOIN shop AS T2 ON T1.Shop_ID  =  T2.Shop_ID GROUP BY T1.Shop_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column4: List all ship names in the order of built year and class.
